      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2 for MRL 3 submission.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2) is governed under a documented software quality assurance plan including version control, regression testing, and change management procedures. Achieved Gradation 3 through ISO 9001-compliant QA documentation and audit trail."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Numerical code verification performed using method of manufactured solutions (MMS) for the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations and scalar transport. Observed convergence rates consistent with second-order spatial accuracy. Meets required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation applied across three systematically refined meshes (4M, 12M, 36M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for hemolysis index QoI. Discretization uncertainty bounded at ±3.8%. Exceeds required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions for the FDA benchmark pump are documented in the FDA Critical Path initiative dataset. Flow rates (2.5–7 L/min) and rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM) match the five COU operating points. Boundary conditions replicated from published experimental protocols."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against experimental measurements from three independent laboratories. Mean relative error of 8.4% across all operating points. Comparison metric (E_rel) within acceptance band defined in validation plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate). This QoI directly maps to the COU decision criterion (RH < 1). Secondary QoIs include shear stress distributions and exposure time, which are mechanistically linked to the hemolysis power-law model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is geometrically similar to the subject device. Operating conditions span the clinical CPB envelope. Validation domain overlap with COU is rated as high for flow regime and moderate for exact geometric fidelity."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not evaluated in the current submission phase; deferred to a subsequent credibility assessment cycle.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error beyond discretization (e.g., iterative convergence tolerances, floating-point round-off accumulation, and linear solver residual contributions to QoI uncertainty) was considered beyond the scope of the present submission. No quantitative bounding analysis was performed. Deferred on the basis that prior submissions at MRL 2 did not require this factor; however, no formal scoping argument has been documented to justify omission at MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not evaluated in the current submission phase.",
      "rationale": "Assessment of potential user-introduced errors (incorrect boundary condition specification, misapplication of turbulence model settings, erroneous post-processing of hemolysis integrals) was flagged as beyond scope for this credibility package. The rationale offered is that the analyst team has prior experience with this pump class; however, no formal use-error protocol, checklist review, or independent verification of simulation setup was documented or referenced."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet required level of 3 at MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation) is evaluated against alternative formulations (Arora, Zhang) across the validation dataset. Sensitivity of RH to model form choice quantified. The k-omega SST turbulence closure is justified by prior literature for rotating machinery hemolysis prediction. Model form uncertainty contribution estimated at ±12% of NIH."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity (3.5 mPa·s), density (1060 kg/m³), and hematocrit (40%) are taken from published physiological reference ranges. Geometric inputs derived from FDA-published CAD files. Inlet velocity profiles specified from measured experimental conditions. Input uncertainty propagation performed for ±5% variation in viscosity."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements used for validation were obtained from three independent test facilities using porcine blood samples with hematocrit 35–42%. Sample preparation and measurement protocols are documented per ASTM F1841. Inter-laboratory variability characterised; coefficient of variation 11.2% across facilities."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not evaluated in the current submission phase.",
      "rationale": "A formal equivalency assessment comparing the input parameter space of the validation experiments to the COU operating envelope — including blood analog properties, temperature, and anti-coagulant effects — was not completed. The team noted this as beyond the scope of the current phase, citing resource constraints and the view that the FDA benchmark dataset is sufficiently representative. No quantitative similarity metric or parameter-space mapping was provided to substantiate this claim at MRL 3."
    }
  ],
